# CODEOWNERS — defines who must review changes to specific paths.
# When the ruleset on `main` has "Require review from Code Owners" enabled,
# a PR that touches any path below cannot merge until an owner here approves.
#
# Syntax: <path pattern>   <owner(s)>
# Owners can be @users or @org/teams. In a real org you'd point infra at a
# TEAM (e.g. @your-org/platform-team) so any platform engineer can approve,
# not a single person who becomes a bottleneck.

# All infrastructure code — the platform lead owns this.
/terraform/                 @npraveen436-wq

# The CI/CD definitions themselves are sensitive — guard them too,
# so nobody can quietly weaken the gates by editing the workflows.
/.github/workflows/         @npraveen436-wq
/.github/CODEOWNERS         @npraveen436-wq
